CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 15, 1960, pg. 3 reads: " Fifth Ward Faithful - women all over the country are particularly fascinated by Senator Kennedy. These Fifth Ward political workers above are no exception.  They anxiously awaited his arrival on the Hill last Monday night, along with 10,000 other persons."
TitMainTitle: Crowd of Fifth Ward political workers, including woman wearing Kennedy sash, awaiting arrival of Senator John F. Kennedy during Kennedy - Johnson presidential campaign tour, Hill District
